Interface Cost<MyCost>

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable<MyCost>
All Known Implementing Classes:
TestCost
public interface Cost<MyCost>
extends Comparable<MyCost>

This class is used to represent costs and heuristic values. The reason that this class is not an interface is to force overriding of the equals() and the compareTo() methods.
It is advised to make your Cost implementation an Immutable Class.

Author:
Steven Roose
